    {
      "id": "f85de3dc_ac7cfc65",
      "file_path": "kubernetes/contrib/components/ejbca/templates/deployment.yaml",
      "patchset_number": 11,
      "line": 64,
      "message": "This ENV is needed, because without it EJBCA would create a default End Entity at startup with a generated UID, for example: \n\"DN: CN=dev-ejbca-5b7c5db448-x25r9,O=EJBCA Container Quickstart,UID=c-0grrktuqfkuw78rxq\"\n\nIn ejbca-config.sh script we create our own CA with a hardcoded UID value. The UID is passed in the certificate update request.",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 3699,
        "name": "Joanna Jeremicz",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "joanna.jeremicz@nokia.com",
        "username": "joannajeremicz"
      },
      "updated": "2021-08-18 12:33:24.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": "0f56daab_37088e01",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "id": "c84e74d0_c38d9d5d",
      "file_path": "kubernetes/platform/components/oom-cert-service/resources/test/cmpServers.json",
      "patchset_number": 11,
      "line": 16,
      "message": "The UID is required to identify the CA to perform the certificate update scenario. If it wasn't hardcoded, EJBCA would create a default CA with a random UID.\nShould we move it to values?",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 3699,
